content:
Configure Eligibility Rules and User Access Control for Service Processes

To restrict the visibility of service processes based on department or customer rating, follow these steps:

Create a Product2 record type for service process products.
Create service process definitions in Service Process Studio for the service processes to configure eligibility rules for.
Add service process products to a service catalog.
Group the service process products in your service catalog by creating catalog categories for each line of business they're relevant for.
Assign service processes to catalog categories.
Define the context structure or scenario for determining service process product eligibility using a context definition.
Map the context definition to data sources and activate the definition.
Create a decision table and rule object to determine service process products qualification.
Control the visibility of service processes by creating qualification rules with input criteria that the service process product must meet to be qualified.
Use a qualification rules procedure to evaluate the qualification of service process products using an expression set and context definition.
Add the catalog and qualification rule procedure names in Action Launcher properties for qualified service process products to be visible on the Action Launcher component.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise, and Unlimited Editions with required licenses.
title: Configuring Eligibility Rules in Financial Services Cloud
